  "text": "BEDTIME STORY Believe it or not, your relatives have been humming around North, Central, and South America for about million years! the oldest fossil was found in Germany. which is strange because you're only known to live in the Americas. You are related to birds called swifts. Over time. some hummingbird species have evolved to match the flowers they visit For example. the buff-tailed sicklebill hummingbird has a unique curved bill that matches the curve of its favorite flowers! Early European explorers. such as Christopher Columbus and Jean de Léry. were amazed by hummingbirds when they first visited the They wondered: Were these creatures insects. or were they birds? Scientists still have a lot to learn about you. and new species are still being discovered. Today. the Andes Mountains in South America are home to percent of hummingbird species. I get my good great-great- great-grandparents! Velvet-purple Coronet Hummingbird",
